Aaron Ramsey consulted on Ryan Shawcross - Chris Coleman
Media playback is not supported on this deviceWales manager Chris Coleman says he has discussed the possibility of calling up Ryan Shawcross to the national squad with captain Aaron Ramsey.Ramsey's leg was broken in six places in 2010 after a tackle by Shawcross during a Stoke City v Arsenal Premier League fixture.Coleman says he has yet to approach Shawcross or his Stoke manager Tony Pulis.